hackathon-description-text: THack @ Dublin is the latest stop on Tnooz's global travel hackathon series.

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: Best THack project by a team of 1 or 2 developers.
Best THack project by a team of 1 or 2 developers.
Best THack project as selected by a vote of all of the developers.
TUI Hotelbeds first prize for best use its API by an individual or team of developers is EUR2,000. Second prize is EUR1,000. Third prize is EUR500.
hackathon-prizes.prize-title: TUI Hotelbeds best use of APIs (three prizes)

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: 33Entrepreneurs prize for the best indivdual or team, a visit to its accelerator HQ in Bordeaux, France. Includes EUR500 for travel expenses.
Skyscanner prize for best use of its flight search API, EUR 1,500 in travel vouchers.

hackathon-judging-criteria.judging-criterion: Is the submission a completely new invention? Or is it the most original idea among all of the submissions presented at the event?
Does the submission address one or more the four challenges posed to participants?
Does the submission work as a digital product or service? Is the coding, design and usability superior to competing submissions?
Has the individual or team presented the idea in a clear, concise and understandable manner? Is the presentation focused on the challenge, and does the submission sufficiently illustrate a solution?

hackathon-description-header: Have a big idea that can make travel better? Can you code it over a weekend hackathon? Want to win your share of more than EUR7,000 in prizes? Join us!
